         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Tonning. ¶  21st. Dec. 1840. ¶ My dear Ferdinand. ¶  ¶ Just as we finish the baking there is a chance to send you something — do have a few pieces while nice and fresh. ¶ also sending collar and cloth...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">40.12.21</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Iwanne Müller</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Private hands.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter not found. The text given here was 'Translated in Sydney from the German', and placed in Louise Wehl's scrap-book.</p>
               </note>Tonning.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Tönning.</p>
               </note> 21st. Dec. 1840.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Ferdinand.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Just as we finish the baking there is a chance to send you something — do have a few pieces while nice and fresh.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">also sending collar and cloth.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bertha<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bertha Müller, M's sister.</p>
               </note> and I thank you for Xmas presents. I am happy because it was my wish for a long time to have an autograph book. We want to give you pleasure — collar and cloth are again fashionable — we bought ½ doz. handkerchiefs, which Clara<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Clara Müller, M's sister.</p>
               </note> has hemmed. She asked us to tell you this. (Clara was seven years old at the time)<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">(Clara was ... time) <seg style="font-style: italic; ">is the translator's note</seg>.</p>
               </note> I think you can use them before they are washed, if not, send back.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Grandfather<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Johann Georg Mertens.</p>
               </note> is seriously ill. Uncle came across the Eider and was stuck by the ice — closed in — and carried down 1/2 a mile, at 5.30 people went after him and caught up to him at 8, and as had to go against wind water and ice reached here at midnight. This fright did Grandfather much harm. I am afraid we shall not have him much longer.<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">M's grandfather died in 1844. </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Please dear Ferdinand come, who knows if you will see Grandfather again. To-day he got a Spanish Fly<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">A treatment prepared from the beetle <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Lytta vesicatoria</seg>. See Imms (1960), p. 807.</p>
               </note> on his chest, to remove his pain — more when you come. Bring your other neck cloth and collar and we can have them dyed for you. Still have to pack. Greetings from Uncle, Aunt, Grandmother,<note xml:id="ftn9" type="footnote" n="9">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Johann Ferdinand and Magdalene Mertens, Maria Mertens.</p>
               </note> Bertha[,]<note xml:id="ftn10" type="footnote" n="10">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">editorial addition.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> Clara and your Sister</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Iwanne Müller.</p>
         </div>
